Expense Operating Delivery Charges Embedded Within Sales Price Percent

The percentage of delivery charges paid to contractors and other businesses for outward freight, cartage, delivery and transport services which were embedded within the sales price. Outward freight refers to movement of goods sold by this business and delivered to a third party.
Expense Operating Delivery Charges Separately Invoiced To Customers Percent

The percentage of delivery charges paid to contractors and other businesses for outward freight, cartage, delivery and transport services which were separately invoiced to customers. Outward freight refers to movement of goods sold by this business and delivered to a third party.
Expense Operating Freight And Cartage Associated With Inward Movement Of Goods Percent
The percentage of freight, cartage, delivery and transport expenses paid to other businesses which are associated with the inward movement of goods.
This excludes outward and internal freight, cartage, delivery and transport expenses.
Expense Operating Fuels And Gas To Power Transport And Motor Vehicles Amount
Expenditure on fuels and gas used to power registered transport and motor vehicles.
Expense Operating Rent Leasing Hiring Excluding Transport And Motor Vehicles Amount

All rent, leasing and hiring expenses other than expenditure on transport and motor vehicles. Transport and motor vehicles include all registered vehicles used to transport freight or passengers, pipelines, trailers and containers.
Expense Operating Rent Leasing Hiring Of Transport And Motor Vehicles Amount

Expenditure on the rent, leasing and hiring of transport and motor vehicles without an operator, driver or crew. It includes operating lease payments but excludes finance lease payments. Transport and motor vehicles include all registered vehicles used to transport freight or passengers, pipelines, trailers and containers.
Expense Operating Self Sourced Water Excluding License Fees Amount
The operating costs associated with extracting water from the environment including the extraction, collection and treatment costs.
Expense Operating Transport Vehicle Amount
Expenditure associated with the running of registered and operated transport and motor vehicles, owned or leased by this business.

This excludes fuels and gas expenditure, electricity expenditure, depreciation, running expenses of registered vehicles hired with a driver, running expenses for off-road motor vehicles and rent, leasing and hiring expenses.
Expense Operating Transport Vehicle Excluding Road Water Air Amount
Other transport and motor vehicle running expenses excludes transport and motor vehicle running expenses associated with road, rail, water and air transport running expenses.
This excludes all transport and motor vehicle expenses associated with unregistered vehicles as well as plant and equipment.
Expense Operating Transport Vehicle Other Amount

All transport and motor vehicle running expenses except for petroleum products and other fuel expenses; repair and maintenance expenses; and registration fees and compulsory third party insurance premiums. Transport and motor vehicles include all registered vehicles used to transport freight or passengers, pipelines, trailers and containers.
Expense Operating Transport Vehicle Petroleum Products And Other Fuel Amount
Expenditure on petroleum products and other fuel used to power registered transport and motor vehicles used to transport freight or passengers.
This excludes expenditure on fuel used to power off-road motor vehicles such as forklifts, mobile plant and quarry dump trucks.
Expense Operating Transport Vehicle Registration Fees And Compulsory Third Party Insurance Premiums Amount

Expenditure on registration fees and third party motor vehicle insurance premiums associated with transport and motor vehicles, including pipelines, trailers and containers. Transport and motor vehicles include all registered vehicles used to transport freight or passengers, pipelines, trailers and containers.
Expense Operating Transport Vehicle Repair And Maintenance Amount

Expenditure for the repair and maintenance of transport and motor vehicles. Transport and motor vehicles include all registered vehicles used to transport freight or passengers, pipelines, trailers and containers.
Expense Operating Transport Vehicle Toll Fees Amount

Expenditure on toll fees associated with the running of transport and motor vehicles.
Transport and motor vehicles include all registered vehicles used to transport freight or passengers, pipelines, trailers and containers.
Expense Purchases Electricity For Resale Amount
The cost of acquiring, by payment of money or its equivalent, electricity with the intention to resell it without further processing.
Expense Purchases Fuels And Gas For Resale Amount
The cost of acquiring, by payment of money or its equivalent, fuels and gas with the intention to resell it without further processing.
Expense Purchases Inclusion Of Inward Freight And Cartage Indicator

Indicates whether the amounts reported in total purchases of materials and goods include inward freight and cartage. Inward freight and cartage expenses is expenditure on costs charged to the business for the transport and delivery of goods into the business by rail, air, road or sea.
Expense Purchases Materials Components Containers Packaging Amount
The cost of acquiring materials, components, containers and packaging materials by payment of money or its equivalent.
Expense Purchases Water For Resale Amount
The cost of acquiring, by payment of money or its equivalent, water with the intention to resell it without further processing.
Income Sale Of Goods Recyclable Recoverable Waste Material Amount

The income from sales of waste material which are recyclable or recoverable.
Recyclable waste is defined as waste that can be recovered through processing to produce material with further usage value.
Income Sale Of Goods And Services Including Rent Leasing Hiring Amount
Income from sales of goods; services; delivery charges; and rent, leasing and hiring.
